-- Mundra Port Stock Falls as India Regulator Alleges Environmental Violation
-- B y   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 2010-12-20T07:59:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/mundra-port-stock-falls-as-india-regulator-alleges-environmental-violation.html
Mundra Port and Special Economic
Zone Ltd. fell the most in almost a month in Mumbai trading
after saying it had received a notice from India’s Ministry of
Environment & Forests that said the company had violated coastal
zone rules.  Mundra Port in the filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange said
it hadn’t violated any law.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hemal Savai in Mumbai at 
